    {
      "id": "1944750c-f3ba-80be-af0b-ee313e367d28",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The benefits of collaborative learning have been previously shown both theoretically and empirically. The work wishes to propose a novel way of forming groups via pre-trained word embeddings. The implementation can account for homogenization or heterogenization constraints. Evaluation is done using a dataset of a course in programming.",
      "raw": {
